cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.GR

This paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (AI) based deep learning algorithms for visual blending in convolutional neural networks, which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential value of these algorithms as tools for computational creativity research, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper touches on the generation of novelty and aesthetic quality, which could be related to the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and graphics (cs.GR).
